HEADWORD: Sciuromorpha
<hw>Sci`u*ro*mor"pha</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>sciurus</ets> squirrel + Gr. <grk>morfh`</grk> form.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A tribe of rodents containing the squirrels and
allied animals, such as the gophers, woodchucks, beavers, and
others.</def>⟦br⟧
